Concepts.definition: Any unfavorable or unintended disease, sign, or symptom (including an abnormal laboratory finding) that is temporally associated with the use of a medical treatment or procedure, and that may or may not be considered related to the medical treatment or procedure. Such events can be related to the intervention, dose, route of administration, patient, or caused by an interaction with another drug(s) or procedure(s).

Concepts.definition: Problem associated with the transfer of energy within an electrical network by means of the capacitance between circuit nodes. It occurs when energy is coupled from one circuit to another through an electric field.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Difficult to Maintain
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Problem associated with the user's ability to service a medical device according to the manufacturer specifications relating to a routine device maintenance, i.e., periodic inspection, failure detection, repair, and care of the device to sustain or restore acceptable operating conditions.

PermissibleValues.value: Cleaning Disinfecting or Sterilization Problem during Medical Device Use
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Cleaning Disinfecting or Sterilization Problem during Medical Device Use

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Cleaning Disinfecting or Sterilization Problem during Medical Device Use
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Issue associated with the undesired introduction of impurities to a device, or the insufficient removal of any visible soil, foreign material or organism deposits on the external surfaces, crevices, and joints of a device by a mechanical and/or manual process intended to render the device sterile, safe for handling, and/or for further processes to decontaminate. This issue is restricted to happening at the location where the device is used as opposed to during manufacturer or shipping.

Concepts.definition: Problem associated with the presence of any unexpected foreign substance found in a device, on its surface or in the package materials, which may affect performance or intended use of the device, or problem that compromise effective decontamination of the device.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Unsafe to Use in Environment

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Unsafe to Use in Environment

Concepts.longName: Device Unsafe to Use in Environment
Concepts.definition: Problem associated with environmental condition that results in the unsafe use of the device. (e.g. electromagnetic fields, noise, vibration, microbiological contamination etc.).
